The true hero’s of May Day

I remember when I was a kid with my siblings not having our parents come to our performances because they were too doped up to attend or they were downing. At the time we didn’t understand but as a child, all we care about is feeling that love and support. Shoutout to the parents who always had extra (I wish I remembered your names)and would walk through the crowd specifically to spot out any kids that didn’t get anything😞 I truly went from looking forward to seeing my parents to just looking forward to seeing you instead🥹 Y’all were really out here making a difference because now that I’m an adult I want to offer the same kind of support that you once did to me.

One of my biggest toxic traits when experiencing depression or anxiety is ghosting EVERYONE. This is something I’ve been working on for a while and still haven’t gotten a hold of it as well as most do. I wanna thank each and everyone of you who reached out to check on me during my absence on social media🥹 It means the world to me. Life has been kicking my ass lately and I needed to take a step back to regroup myself. I’m still recovering from the events that took place and I’m excited to be back!!! 

If you’re going through a tough time right now I just wanna extend my love to you at this time to remind you that everything we go through is TEMPORARY. It will pass. Surround yourself with those who love and support you and cut off all others. Love you all and I wish everyone a blessed week🫶🏽

#mentalhealthawareness #support #mentalhealth #fightingdepression #survivor

Found this in my drafts🥺 This is what depression partially looked like for me over these past 4 months. Some days I’m up and some I’m DOWN DOWN. I was actually about to delete this draft but then I realized I should share with you all the raw side of me because life isn’t all sunshine and rainbows like social media paints it out to be. 

I remember the day I made this. I was sick of the economy and the effects it’s had on Hawaii in general. My intention was to talk about how hypocritical it is for our government to talk about how businesses were struggling to find employees yet the requirements were ridiculous while the wage was unlivable. The State of Hawaii homeless rate is one of the highest in the country yet we are the smallest. At this time I was working 7 days a week with about 6 hours of sleep if I wasn’t up all night from insomnia. I was brought up by a long line of drug addicts and alcoholics and promised myself that as an adult, I will do everything in my power to break that vicious cycle. Both me and my sister @iamari92 did but do you even know how hard it is to not have any guidance?But we did it and I promise you I will keep going till the end. 

On this particular day though, @prestyncarrizosa  just took our son out on my first day off in over 30 days so I could rest. My son was complaining that he doesn’t see me anymore and so much more. To have my own son ask me if I could spend time with him hurt me so much to where once I hit the  record button I just cracked. I’ve never had him feel the need to even ask me that before.

This is what it was like for me everytime I attempted to make content. Trying to keep up with social media is a whole job in itself and I’m done trying to be perfect because I’m just not. I stopped working as much since then and slowly putting the puzzle pieces back together to see if any new paths present themselves. Moving forward I want to welcome each of you who are a little broken just like me. You are not alone❤️Imma still be my normal goofy self but while I heal I hope to keep you all here with me🥹
